Interface BoardInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public interface BoardInterface
extends java.lang.Cloneable
    BoardInterface represents the board state in the game of tabula (not including dice and players). Requires a constructor with no parameters which creates and initialises all of the locations for the start of the game.

      • takeTurn

        void takeTurn(Colour colour,
              TurnInterface turn,
              java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> diceValues)
       throws IllegalTurnException
        Update the Board state by making the all of the moves in the given turn in order, including any knocking off, based on the given diceValues.
        Parameters:
        colour - the colour to move
        turn - the turn to take
        diceValues - the values of the dice available in no particular order. There will be repeated values in the list if a double is thrown
        Throws:
        IllegalTurnException - if and only if the turns in the move are not legal for the diceValues give. Each of the moves has to be legal, and the diceValues in the moves of the turn must match the diceValues parameter. The number of moves in the turn must be no less than the maximum possible number of legal moves: all available dice must be used. If IllegalTurnException is thrown then the board state remains unchanged.
